# Git workflow (Tavily_dashborad)

At the **end of each iteration** (when a coherent change is done), **commit and push** to `origin`:

1. `git add` the files you changed (avoid unrelated files).
2. `git commit -m "..."` with a short, accurate message.
3. `git push`.

If `git` is not on PATH (Windows), use the full path to Git, e.g. `C:\Program Files\Git\bin\git.exe`, with `-C` set to this repo root.

Do not leave finished work uncommitted unless the user explicitly wants a WIP kept local.
